summary: i think i realized why im such a hardcore phillie
body:
i think i realized why im such a hardcore phillie

1) we have a lot of things in common: we are both a bit childish, kind-hearted, laugh a lot, and put other people (friends and family) first

2) i look up to him: the man decided to follow his heart and is now a successful entertainer, he found his soulmate, is really mature, has strong opinions, is really damn intelligent (i am studying the same career he studied and that shit hard)

3) even tho i have my doubts about astrology that shit creeped me out: we share a lot of traits of pisces, not gonna go into detail but theyre weirdly accurate

summary: we really are so lucky to have dan and phil for a lot of reasons, but one that really sticks out to me is their willingness to...
body:
we really are so lucky to have dan and phil for a lot of reasons, but one that really sticks out to me is their willingness to use they/them pronouns for anyone whose gender they don’t know. most other youtubers don’t do that, and if they do, they’re not nearly as consistent as dnp. when they invited people onto the rize streams, when they read liveshow comments, when they talk about moments with fans, they always use they/them.

not only does that show respect to their fans’ identities, it also shows a recognition of how many of their fans are lgbt+. on top of that, they’re helping to normalize using they/them even for people who may be cis, rather than just the people whose gender you can’t tell right off the bat.

dnp are endlessly supportive of the lgbt community & respect the hell out of their fans and i live for it
